title: Genesis (JPSA)
creator: Jewish Publication Society of America
description: LibriVox recording of The Holy Scriptures According To The Masoretic Text A New Translation: Genesis by The Jewish Publication Society of America (1917). The first book of the Pentateuch - Genesis. Presented according to weekly parshah. Praised are You, Adonai, Our G-d, ruler of the Universe, who has made us holy with commandments and commanded us to engage in the study of Torah. (Summary by Linette Geisel and traditional prayer) Parshat descriptions provided by Wikipedia. For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: librivox; literature; audiobook; ancient texts; religion
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
